divs: Sighting DetailsI was just taking pictures of the sunset when I noticed what appeared to be a descending cloud high in the sky. I knew that it could not be a cloud because once it was low enough it began to glow perhaps from the sun's rays in the background. I at that point took another picture of it as it was positioned in another area of downtown or perhaps it was another object. In any event it was no longer ciruclar. It was now L shaped.
Summary: Circular object cloud like that became L shaped. or Perhaps 2 objects.
